text: Pedinogyra rotabilis is a species of air-breathing land snail, a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Caryodidae. Distribution map of Pedinogyra rotabilis ==Distribution== This species is endemic to Australia. ==References== ==External links== * http://www.environment.gov.au/biodiversity/abrs/online- resources/fauna/afd/taxa/7de43552-0694-47a4-b858-db3a76ba63f0 Category:Caryodidae Category:Gastropods described in 1852
title: Pedinogyra rotabilis
